'''''Nartissteu''''' was the name of a [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] [[Freighter/Legends|freighter]] based out of [[Nellac Kram]].

In [[9 ABY/Legends|9 ABY]], [[Grand Admiral/Legends|Grand Admiral]] [[Mitth'raw'nuruodo/Legends|Thrawn's]] forces illegally appropriated the ''Nartissteu''{{'s}} identification and used it as an alias for an [[A-class bulk freighter]] in [[Thrawn's fleet (Galactic Empire)|Thrawn's fleet]] during the [[Battle of Sluis Van]].

The ersatz ''Nartissteu'' arrived at the [[Sluis Van Shipyards]] before the rest of the [[Galactic Empire/Legends|Imperial]] fleet with apparent damage and a seemingly empty cargo bay. The ship had reported to Sluis Control that it had been damaged in a pirate attack that caused them to dump all their cargo. The ship was then to await repairs.

In fact, the freighter carried [[Cloaking device/Legends|cloaked]] [[TIE/ln space superiority starfighter/Legends|TIEs]] and the damage it had sustained was probably a cover for the fact that it was set to explode.

[[Commander/Legends|Commander]] [[Wedge Antilles/Legends|Wedge Antilles]] of [[Rogue Squadron/Legends|Rogue Squadron]] and [[Captain/Legends|Captain]] [[Afyon]], both aboard the [[New Republic/Legends|New Republic]] ship ''[[Larkhess]]'' noticed that something was strange about the ship and Rogue Squadron launched. The [[T-65 X-wing starfighter/Legends|X-Wing]] pilots were first on the scene when the ''Nartissteu'' self-destructed, allowing the TIEs hidden in her hold to launch their surprise attack and beginning the [[Battle of Sluis Van]].

